hy L Sayers nut!). There was even a reference to <a href="https://goodreads.com/book/show/21787.The_Princess_Bride_" title="The Princess Bride  by William Goldman" rel="noopener">The Princess Bride</a>, or at least I think there was. <input type="checkbox" class="spoiler__control" aria-label="The following text has been marked spoiler. Toggle checkbox to reveal or hide." onchange="this.labels[0].setAttribute('aria-hidden', !this.checked);" id="9bddc6cb-2ac4-4e76-99a6-df083fa7e270" /><label aria-hidden="true" class="spoiler" for="9bddc6cb-2ac4-4e76-99a6-df083fa7e270"> A character saying "As you wish" more than once to a young lady struck me as a clue. </label><br /><br />I absolutely loved reading this, all the more so because I took the advice of some GR reviewers and read <a href="https://goodreads.com/book/show/4921.Three_Men_in_a_Boat" title="Three Men in a Boat by Jerome K. Jerome" rel="noopener">Three Men in a Boat</a> first. It's not essential to do so, but I'm very glad I did. This was the ideal novel to read while on holidays and I want to read it again. Here's to serendipitous random clicking, <i>The Guardian</i> and the expansion of literary boundaries brought to me courtesy of Goodreads. </span></div></div></div></section></section><section class="ReviewCard__tags"><ul class="CollapsableList"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/4542979?shelf=all-time-favourites" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">all-time-favourites</span></a> <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/4542979?shelf=kindle" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">kindle</span></a></ul></section><footer class="SocialFooter"><div data-testid="stats" class="SocialFooter__statsContainer"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">36 likes</span></button></div><div class="Button__container"><but